{
  "texts": [
    "adds Gaussian noise with zero mean and 0.1 standard deviation to standardized attributes.Specifically, we conduct the process below for each column j ∈ {1,..., p}:z ij = x ij -µ j σ j, z ′ ij = z ij + ϵ • N (0, 1), x ′ ij = z ′ ij • σ j + µ j,where ϵ = 0.1 is the attack strength, and µ j and σ j are the empirical mean and standard deviation of column j in the original data.",
    "Conducting round and clip if x ′ ij is not in the valid range of column j in the original data. 7.",
    "Truncation.",
    "truncates numerical values at the first significant digit. 8.",
    "Quantization."
  ]
}